Speech: So that is where my income limit would trigger.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: Right.
Speech: Right.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: My plan -
Speech: My plan -
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: --notwithstanding my opponent's ad, my plan triggers in at gross incomes, family incomes of $200,000 and above.
Speech: --notwithstanding my opponent's ad, my plan triggers in at gross incomes, family incomes of $200,000 and above.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Then we want to give modest middle-class tax relief to restore some fairness, especially to middle- class people with families with incomes of under $60,000.
Speech: Then we want to give modest middle-class tax relief to restore some fairness, especially to middle- class people with families with incomes of under $60,000.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: In addition to that, the money that I raise from upper-income people and from asking foreign corporations just to pay the same income on their income earned in America that American corporations do will be used to give incentives back to upper-income people.
Speech: In addition to that, the money that I raise from upper-income people and from asking foreign corporations just to pay the same income on their income earned in America that American corporations do will be used to give incentives back to upper-income people.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I want to give people permanent incentives on investment tax credit, like President Kennedy and the Congress inaugurated in the early '60s to get industry moving again; a research and development tax credit; a low-income housing tax credit; a long-term capital gains proposal for new business and business expansions.
Speech: I want to give people permanent incentives on investment tax credit, like President Kennedy and the Congress inaugurated in the early '60s to get industry moving again; a research and development tax credit; a low-income housing tax credit; a long-term capital gains proposal for new business and business expansions.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've got to have no more trickle down.
Speech: We've got to have no more trickle down.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We don't need across-the-board tax cuts for the wealthy for nothing.
Speech: We don't need across-the-board tax cuts for the wealthy for nothing.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We need to say here's your tax incentive: if you create American jobs, the old-fashioned way.
Speech: We need to say here's your tax incentive: if you create American jobs, the old-fashioned way.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'd like to create more millionaires than were created under Mr. Bush and Mr. Reagan, but I don't want to have 4 years where we have no growth in the private sector, and that's what's happened in the last 4 years.
Speech: I'd like to create more millionaires than were created under Mr. Bush and Mr. Reagan, but I don't want to have 4 years where we have no growth in the private sector, and that's what's happened in the last 4 years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We're down 35,000 jobs in the private sector.
Speech: We're down 35,000 jobs in the private sector.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We need to invest and grow, and that's what I want to do.
Speech: We need to invest and grow, and that's what I want to do.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: BUSH: Well, let me--I have to correct one thing.
Speech: Well, let me--I have to correct one thing.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I didn't question the man's patriotism.
Speech: I didn't question the man's patriotism.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I questioned his judgment and his character.
Speech: I questioned his judgment and his character.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: What he did in Moscow, that's fine.
Speech: What he did in Moscow, that's fine.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Let him explain it.
Speech: Let him explain it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: He did.
Speech: He did.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I accept that.
Speech: I accept that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: What I don't accept is demonstrating and organizing demonstrations in a foreign country when your country's at war.
Speech: What I don't accept is demonstrating and organizing demonstrations in a foreign country when your country's at war.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I'm sorry.
Speech: I'm sorry.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I cannot accept that.
Speech: I cannot accept that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: In terms of this one on taxes spells out the biggest difference between us.
Speech: In terms of this one on taxes spells out the biggest difference between us.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I do not believe we need to go back to the Mondale proposals or the Dukakis proposals of tax and spend.
Speech: I do not believe we need to go back to the Mondale proposals or the Dukakis proposals of tax and spend.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Governor Clinton says $200,000 but he also says he wants to raise $150 billion.
Speech: Governor Clinton says $200,000 but he also says he wants to raise $150 billion.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Taxing people over $200,000 will not get you $150 billion.
Speech: Taxing people over $200,000 will not get you $150 billion.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And then when you add in his other spending proposals, regrettably you end up socking it to the working man.
Speech: And then when you add in his other spending proposals, regrettably you end up socking it to the working man.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: That old adage they use--we're going to soak the rich- -we're going to soak the rich--it always ends up being the poor cab driver or the working man that ends up paying the bill.
Speech: That old adage they use--we're going to soak the rich- -we're going to soak the rich--it always ends up being the poor cab driver or the working man that ends up paying the bill.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And so I just have a different approach.
Speech: And so I just have a different approach.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I believe the way to get the deficit down is to control the growth of mandatory spending programs, and not raise taxes on the American people.
Speech: I believe the way to get the deficit down is to control the growth of mandatory spending programs, and not raise taxes on the American people.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We've got a big difference there.
Speech: We've got a big difference there.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: PEROT: We've got to have a growing, expanding job base to give us a growing, expanding tax base.
Speech: We've got to have a growing, expanding job base to give us a growing, expanding tax base.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Right now we have a flat to deteriorating job base and where it appears to be growing, it's minimum-wage jobs.
Speech: Right now we have a flat to deteriorating job base and where it appears to be growing, it's minimum-wage jobs.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: So we've got to really rebuild our job base.
Speech: So we've got to really rebuild our job base.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: That's going to take money for infrastructure and investment to do that.
Speech: That's going to take money for infrastructure and investment to do that.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Our foreign competitors are doing it; we're not.
Speech: Our foreign competitors are doing it; we're not.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We cannot pay off the $4 trillion debt, balance the budget and have the industries of the future and the high- paying jobs in this country without having the revenue.
Speech: We cannot pay off the $4 trillion debt, balance the budget and have the industries of the future and the high- paying jobs in this country without having the revenue.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We're going to go through a period of shared sacrifice.
Speech: We're going to go through a period of shared sacrifice.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: There's one challenge.
Speech: There's one challenge.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It's got to be fair.
Speech: It's got to be fair.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We've created a mess, don't have much to show for it and we have got to fix it.
Speech: We've created a mess, don't have much to show for it and we have got to fix it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And that's about all I can say in a minute.
Speech: And that's about all I can say in a minute.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: BUSH: Well, Sander, that's a good question, and the answer is: for 40-some years we kept the peace.
Speech: Well, Sander, that's a good question, and the answer is: for 40-some years we kept the peace.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: If you look at the cost of not keeping the peace in Europe, it would be exorbitant.
Speech: If you look at the cost of not keeping the peace in Europe, it would be exorbitant.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We have reduced the number of troops that are deployed and going to be deployed.
Speech: We have reduced the number of troops that are deployed and going to be deployed.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I have cut defense spending.
Speech: I have cut defense spending.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And the reason we could do that is because of our fantastic success in winning the Cold War.
Speech: And the reason we could do that is because of our fantastic success in winning the Cold War.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We never would have got there if we had gone for the nuclear freeze crowd; we never would have got there if we had listened to those that wanted to cut defense spending.
Speech: We never would have got there if we had gone for the nuclear freeze crowd; we never would have got there if we had listened to those that wanted to cut defense spending.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I think it is important that the US stay in Europe and continue to guarantee the peace.
Speech: I think it is important that the US stay in Europe and continue to guarantee the peace.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We simply cannot pull back.
Speech: We simply cannot pull back.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Now, when anybody has a spending program they want to spend money on at home, they say, well, let's cut money out of the Defense Dept.
Speech: Now, when anybody has a spending program they want to spend money on at home, they say, well, let's cut money out of the Defense Dept.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I will accept and have accepted the recommendations of 2 proven leaders, General Colin Powell and Secretary Dick Cheney.
Speech: I will accept and have accepted the recommendations of 2 proven leaders, General Colin Powell and Secretary Dick Cheney.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: They feel that the levels we're operating at and the reductions that I have proposed are proper.
Speech: They feel that the levels we're operating at and the reductions that I have proposed are proper.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And so I simply do not think we should go back to the isolation days and starting blaming foreigners.
Speech: And so I simply do not think we should go back to the isolation days and starting blaming foreigners.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We are the sole remaining superpower, and we should be that.
Speech: We are the sole remaining superpower, and we should be that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And we have a certain disproportionate responsibility.
Speech: And we have a certain disproportionate responsibility.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But I would ask the American people to understand that if we make imprudent cuts, if we go too far, we risk the peace.
Speech: But I would ask the American people to understand that if we make imprudent cuts, if we go too far, we risk the peace.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And I don't want to do that.
Speech: And I don't want to do that.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I've seen what it is like to see a war, to see the burdens of a war, and I don't want to see us make reckless cuts.
Speech: I've seen what it is like to see a war, to see the burdens of a war, and I don't want to see us make reckless cuts.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Because of our programs we have been able to significantly cut defense spending.
Speech: Because of our programs we have been able to significantly cut defense spending.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But let's not cut into the muscle, and let's not cut down our insurance policy, which is participation of American forces in NATO, the greatest peace- keeping organization ever made.
Speech: But let's not cut into the muscle, and let's not cut down our insurance policy, which is participation of American forces in NATO, the greatest peace- keeping organization ever made.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Today you've got problems in Europe, still bubbling along even though Europe's gone democracy's route.
Speech: Today you've got problems in Europe, still bubbling along even though Europe's gone democracy's route.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But we are there, and I think this insurance policy is necessary.
Speech: But we are there, and I think this insurance policy is necessary.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I think it goes with world leadership, and I think the levels we've come up with are just about right.
Speech: I think it goes with world leadership, and I think the levels we've come up with are just about right.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: PEROT: If I'm poor and you're rich, and I can get you to defend me, that's good.
Speech: If I'm poor and you're rich, and I can get you to defend me, that's good.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: But when the tables get turned, I ought to do my share.
Speech: But when the tables get turned, I ought to do my share.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Right now we spend about $300 billion a year on defense, the Japanese spend around 30 billion in Asia, the Germans spend around 30 billion in Europe.
Speech: Right now we spend about $300 billion a year on defense, the Japanese spend around 30 billion in Asia, the Germans spend around 30 billion in Europe.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: For example, Germany will spend a trillion dollars building infrastructure over the next 10 years.
Speech: For example, Germany will spend a trillion dollars building infrastructure over the next 10 years.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It's kind of easy to do if you only have to pick up a $30-billion tab to defend your country.
Speech: It's kind of easy to do if you only have to pick up a $30-billion tab to defend your country.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: The European Community is in a position to pay a lot more than they have in the past.
Speech: The European Community is in a position to pay a lot more than they have in the past.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I agree with the president: when they couldn't, we should have; now that they can, they should.
Speech: I agree with the president: when they couldn't, we should have; now that they can, they should.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We sort of seem to have a desire to try to stay over there and control it.
Speech: We sort of seem to have a desire to try to stay over there and control it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: They don't want us to control it, very candidly.
Speech: They don't want us to control it, very candidly.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: So it I think is very important for us to let them assume more and more of the burden and for us to bring that money back here and rebuild our infrastructure, because we can only be a superpower if we are an economic superpower; and we can only be an economic superpower if we have a growing, expanding job base.
Speech: So it I think is very important for us to let them assume more and more of the burden and for us to bring that money back here and rebuild our infrastructure, because we can only be a superpower if we are an economic superpower; and we can only be an economic superpower if we have a growing, expanding job base.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: I agree with the general statement Mr. Bush made.
Speech: I agree with the general statement Mr. Bush made.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I disagree that we need 150,000 troops to fulfill our role in Europe.
Speech: I disagree that we need 150,000 troops to fulfill our role in Europe.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We certainly must maintain an engagement there.
Speech: We certainly must maintain an engagement there.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: There are certainly dangers there, there are certainly other trouble spots in the world which are closer to Europe than to the US.
Speech: There are certainly dangers there, there are certainly other trouble spots in the world which are closer to Europe than to the US.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But 2 former defense secretaries recently issued a report saying that 100,000 or slightly fewer troops would be enough, including President Reagan's former defense secretary, Mr. Carlucci.
Speech: But 2 former defense secretaries recently issued a report saying that 100,000 or slightly fewer troops would be enough, including President Reagan's former defense secretary, Mr. Carlucci.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Many of the military experts whom I consulted on this agreed.
Speech: Many of the military experts whom I consulted on this agreed.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We're going to have to spend more money in the future on military technology and on greater mobility, greater airlift, greater sealift, the B-22 airplane.
Speech: We're going to have to spend more money in the future on military technology and on greater mobility, greater airlift, greater sealift, the B-22 airplane.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We're going to have to do some things that are quite costly.
Speech: We're going to have to do some things that are quite costly.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I simply don't believe we can afford nor do we need to keep 150,000 troops in Europe given how much the Red Army, now under the control of Russia, has been cut, the arms control agreement concluded between Mr. Bush and Mr. Yeltsin, something I have applauded.
Speech: And I simply don't believe we can afford nor do we need to keep 150,000 troops in Europe given how much the Red Army, now under the control of Russia, has been cut, the arms control agreement concluded between Mr. Bush and Mr. Yeltsin, something I have applauded.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I don't think we need 150,000 troops.
Speech: I don't think we need 150,000 troops.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let me make one other point.
Speech: Let me make one other point.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Mr. Bush talked about taxes.
Speech: Mr. Bush talked about taxes.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: He didn't tell you that he vetoed a middle class tax cut because it would be paid for by raising taxes on the wealthy and vetoed an investment tax credit paid for by raising taxes on the wealthy.
Speech: He didn't tell you that he vetoed a middle class tax cut because it would be paid for by raising taxes on the wealthy and vetoed an investment tax credit paid for by raising taxes on the wealthy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: PEROT: It's 10 cents a year cumulative.
Speech: It's 10 cents a year cumulative.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It finally gets to 50 cents at the end of the 5th year.
Speech: It finally gets to 50 cents at the end of the 5th year.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I think "punish" is the wrong word.
Speech: I think "punish" is the wrong word.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Again, see, I didn't create this problem.
Speech: Again, see, I didn't create this problem.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We're trying to solve it.
Speech: We're trying to solve it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Now, if you study our international competitors, some of our international competitors collect up to $3.50 a gallon in taxes, and they use that money to build infrastructure and to create jobs.
Speech: Now, if you study our international competitors, some of our international competitors collect up to $3.50 a gallon in taxes, and they use that money to build infrastructure and to create jobs.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We collect 35 cents, and we don't have it to spend.
Speech: We collect 35 cents, and we don't have it to spend.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I know it's not popular, and I understand the nature of your question.
Speech: I know it's not popular, and I understand the nature of your question.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: But the people who will be helped the most by it are the working people who will get the jobs created because of this tax.
Speech: But the people who will be helped the most by it are the working people who will get the jobs created because of this tax.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Why do we have to do it?
Speech: Why do we have to do it?
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Because we have so mismanaged our country over the years, and it is now time to pay the fiddler.
Speech: Because we have so mismanaged our country over the years, and it is now time to pay the fiddler.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: And if we don't, we will be spending our children's money.
Speech: And if we don't, we will be spending our children's money.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We have spent $4 trillion worth.
Speech: We have spent $4 trillion worth.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: An incredible number of young people are active in supporting my effort because they are deeply concerned that we have taken the American dream from them.
Speech: An incredible number of young people are active in supporting my effort because they are deeply concerned that we have taken the American dream from them.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: I think it's fitting that we're on the campus of a university tonight.
Speech: I think it's fitting that we're on the campus of a university tonight.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: These young people, when they get out of this wonderful university, will have difficulty finding a job.
Speech: These young people, when they get out of this wonderful university, will have difficulty finding a job.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We've got to clean this mess up, leave this country in good shape, and pass on the American dream to them.
Speech: We've got to clean this mess up, leave this country in good shape, and pass on the American dream to them.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We've got to collect the taxes to do it.
Speech: We've got to collect the taxes to do it.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If there's a fairer way, I'm all ears (laughter) --aah.
Speech: If there's a fairer way, I'm all ears (laughter) --aah.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: (Laughter and applause) But--but--see, let me make it very clear.
Speech: (Laughter and applause) But--but--see, let me make it very clear.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If people don't have the stomach to fix these problems, I think it's a good time to face it, November.
Speech: If people don't have the stomach to fix these problems, I think it's a good time to face it, November.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: If they do, then they will have heard the harsh reality of what we have to do.
Speech: If they do, then they will have heard the harsh reality of what we have to do.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Speech: I'm not playing Lawrence Welk music tonight.

Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON: I think Mr. Perot has confronted this deficit issue, but I think it's important to point out that we really have 2 deficits in America, not one.
Speech: I think Mr. Perot has confronted this deficit issue, but I think it's important to point out that we really have 2 deficits in America, not one.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have a budget deficit in the federal government, but we also have an investment, a jobs, an income deficit.
Speech: We have a budget deficit in the federal government, but we also have an investment, a jobs, an income deficit.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: People are working harder for less money than they were making 10 years ago, 2- 3rds of our people--a $1600 drop in average income in just the last 2 years.

Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The problem I have with the Perot prescription is that almost all economists who've looked at it say that if you cut the deficit this much this quick it will increase unemployment, it will slow down the economy.
Speech: The problem I have with the Perot prescription is that almost all economists who've looked at it say that if you cut the deficit this much this quick it will increase unemployment, it will slow down the economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's why I think we shouldn't do it that quickly.
Speech: That's why I think we shouldn't do it that quickly.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have a disciplined reduction in the deficit of 50 % over the next 4 years, but first get incentives to invest in this economy, put the American people back to work.
Speech: We have a disciplined reduction in the deficit of 50 % over the next 4 years, but first get incentives to invest in this economy, put the American people back to work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've got to invest and grow.
Speech: We've got to invest and grow.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: 9 Nobel Prize-winning economists and 500 others, including numerous Republican and Democratic business executives, have endorsed this approach because it offers the best hope to put America back to work and get our incomes rising instead of falling.
Speech: 9 Nobel Prize-winning economists and 500 others, including numerous Republican and Democratic business executives, have endorsed this approach because it offers the best hope to put America back to work and get our incomes rising instead of falling.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: BUSH: Your question was on fairness.
Speech: Your question was on fairness.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I just disagree with Mr. Perot.
Speech: I just disagree with Mr. Perot.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I don't believe it is fair to slap a 50-cent-a-gallon tax over whatever many years on the people that have to drive for a living, people that go long distances.
Speech: I don't believe it is fair to slap a 50-cent-a-gallon tax over whatever many years on the people that have to drive for a living, people that go long distances.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I don't think we need to do it.
Speech: I don't think we need to do it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: You see, I have a fundamental difference.
Speech: You see, I have a fundamental difference.
Speaker: BUSH

Text: American airplanes are helping today on humanitarian relief for Sarajevo.
Speech: American airplanes are helping today on humanitarian relief for Sarajevo.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: It is America that's in the lead in helping with humanitarian relief for Somalia.
Speech: It is America that's in the lead in helping with humanitarian relief for Somalia.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But when you go to put somebody else's son or daughter into war, I think you got to be a little bit careful and you have to be sure that there's a military plan that can do this.
Speech: But when you go to put somebody else's son or daughter into war, I think you got to be a little bit careful and you have to be sure that there's a military plan that can do this.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: You have ancient ethnic rivalries that have cropped up as Yugoslavia's dissolved or getting dissolved, and it isn't going to be solved by sending in the 82nd Airborne, and I'm not going to do that as commander-in-chief.
Speech: You have ancient ethnic rivalries that have cropped up as Yugoslavia's dissolved or getting dissolved, and it isn't going to be solved by sending in the 82nd Airborne, and I'm not going to do that as commander-in-chief.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I am going to stand by and use the moral persuasion of the US to get satisfaction in terms of prison camps, and we're making some progress there, and in terms of getting humanitarian relief in there.
Speech: I am going to stand by and use the moral persuasion of the US to get satisfaction in terms of prison camps, and we're making some progress there, and in terms of getting humanitarian relief in there.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And right now, as you know, the US took the lead in a no-fly operation up there in-- no- fly order up in the United Nations.
Speech: And right now, as you know, the US took the lead in a no-fly operation up there in-- no- fly order up in the United Nations.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: We're working through the international organizations.
Speech: We're working through the international organizations.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: That's one thing I learned by forging that tremendous and greatly--highly successful coalition against Saddam Hussein, the dictator.
Speech: That's one thing I learned by forging that tremendous and greatly--highly successful coalition against Saddam Hussein, the dictator.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: Use--work internationally to do it.
Speech: Use--work internationally to do it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I am very concerned about it.
Speech: I am very concerned about it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I am concerned about ethnic cleansing.
Speech: I am concerned about ethnic cleansing.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: I am concerned about a tax on Muslims, for example, over there.
Speech: I am concerned about a tax on Muslims, for example, over there.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: But I must stop short of using American force until I know how those young men and women are going to get out of there as well as get in, know what the mission is, and define it.
Speech: But I must stop short of using American force until I know how those young men and women are going to get out of there as well as get in, know what the mission is, and define it.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: And I think I'm on the right track.
Speech: And I think I'm on the right track.
Speaker: BUSH
Name: George H. W. Bush

Text: PEROT: I think if we learned anything in Vietnam is you first commit this nation before you commit the troops to the battlefield.
Speech: I think if we learned anything in Vietnam is you first commit this nation before you commit the troops to the battlefield.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: We cannot send our people all over the world to solve every problem that comes up.
Speech: We cannot send our people all over the world to solve every problem that comes up.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: This is basically a problem that is a primary concern to the European Community.
Speech: This is basically a problem that is a primary concern to the European Community.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Certainly we care about the people, we care about the children, we care about the tragedy.
Speech: Certainly we care about the people, we care about the children, we care about the tragedy.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: But it is inappropriate for us, just because there's a problem somewhere around the world, to take the sons and daughters of working people--and make no mistake about it, our all- volunteer armed force is not made up of the sons and daughters of the beautiful people; it's the working folks who send their sons and daughters to war, with a few exceptions.
Speech: But it is inappropriate for us, just because there's a problem somewhere around the world, to take the sons and daughters of working people--and make no mistake about it, our all- volunteer armed force is not made up of the sons and daughters of the beautiful people; it's the working folks who send their sons and daughters to war, with a few exceptions.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It's very unlike World War II, when FDR's sons flew missions.
Speech: It's very unlike World War II, when FDR's sons flew missions.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: Everybody went.
Speech: Everybody went.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It's a different world now.
Speech: It's a different world now.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: It's very important that we not just, without thinking it through, just rush to every problem in the world and have our people torn to pieces.
Speech: It's very important that we not just, without thinking it through, just rush to every problem in the world and have our people torn to pieces.
Speaker: PEROT
Name: Henry Ross Perot

Text: CLINTON:  I agree that we cannot commit ground forces to become involved in the quagmire of Bosnia or in the tribal wars of Somalia.
Speech: I agree that we cannot commit ground forces to become involved in the quagmire of Bosnia or in the tribal wars of Somalia.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I think that it's important to recognize that there are things that can be done short of that, and that we do have interests there.
Speech: But I think that it's important to recognize that there are things that can be done short of that, and that we do have interests there.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: There are, after all, 2 million refugees now because of the problems in what was Yugoslavia, the largest number since World War II, and there may be hundreds of thousands of people who will starve or freeze to death in this winter.
Speech: There are, after all, 2 million refugees now because of the problems in what was Yugoslavia, the largest number since World War II, and there may be hundreds of thousands of people who will starve or freeze to death in this winter.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The US should try to work with its allies and stop it.
Speech: The US should try to work with its allies and stop it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I urged the president to support this air cover, and he did--and I applaud that.
Speech: I urged the president to support this air cover, and he did--and I applaud that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I applaud the no-fly zone, and I know that he's going back to the United Nations to try to get authority to enforce it.
Speech: I applaud the no-fly zone, and I know that he's going back to the United Nations to try to get authority to enforce it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think we should stiffen the embargo on the Belgrade government, and I think we have to consider whether or not we should lift the arms embargo now on the Bosnians, since they are in no way in a fair fight with a heavily armed opponent bent on ethnic cleansing.
Speech: I think we should stiffen the embargo on the Belgrade government, and I think we have to consider whether or not we should lift the arms embargo now on the Bosnians, since they are in no way in a fair fight with a heavily armed opponent bent on ethnic cleansing.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We can't get involved in the quagmire, but we must do what we can.
Speech: We can't get involved in the quagmire, but we must do what we can.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton
